AMBOR1M.title: 1-Month AMERIBOR Term Structure of Interest Rates
AMBOR1M.notes:
AMERIBOR® (American Interbank Offered Rate) is a benchmark interest rate based on overnight unsecured loans transacted on the American Financial Exchange (AFX). AMERIBOR® is calculated as the transaction volume weighted average interest rate of the daily transactions in the AMERIBOR® overnight unsecured loan market on the AFX. The arbitrage free AMERIBOR® Term Structure of Interest Rates is derived from the Overnight Unsecured AMERIBOR® Interest Rate (AMERIBOR (https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/AMERIBOR)) and the implied AMERIBOR® forward rates from the AMERIBOR® futures prices. More details about AMERIBOR® methodology can be found on the source's website (https://ameribor.net), under the Resources section.

AMERIBOR® is a registered trademark of the American Financial Exchange (AFX). © Copyright, American Financial Exchange (AFX). All Rights Reserved.
